  "texts": [
    "MM lesions typically showed low signal in T1-weighted images, high signal in T2-weighted images, and often enhanced signal in vanadium enhanced images.",
    "On the WB-DWI images, the diffusion of MM lesions was limited and showed a high signal.",
    "The apparent diffusion coefficient (ADC) could be used to quantify the moisture diffusion.",
    "The m DIXON technique can be used to quantify bone marrow fat content by fat fraction (FF).",
    "IVIM technology can quantify the diffusion and perfusion of bone marrow[8] Application of Different MRI Sequences in MM-MRD PrognosisThe conventional MRI sequences used to evaluate MM bone marrow infiltration were T1 weighted,T2 weighted lipid-enhanced, and TI weighted lipid-enhanced."
